    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - PAINT AND REFINISHING - ORIGINAL FINISH RESTORATION -
        POLISHING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>POLISHING</title>
        <para>To restore gloss and remove swirl marks, polishing compounds are used. These are formulated for hand and
            machine application. Polishing compounds seldom contain course abrasives, however caution should be
            exercised when machine polishing so as to not damage the finish from heat build-up.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
